\gcd(k,n)
 \sum_{x \in \mathbb{Z}/n \mathbb{Z}} e\left(\frac{kx^2}{n} \right) = \left\{ \begin{array}{lcl} \varepsilon_n \left( \frac{k}{n} \right) \sqrt{n} & & n \equiv 1 \pmod{2}\\ 0 & &  n \equiv 2\pmod{4}\\ (1 + i) \varepsilon_k^{-1} \left(\frac{n}{k} \right)\sqrt{n} & & k \equiv 1 \pmod{2}, 4 \mid n \end{array}\right. 
 \varepsilon_m = \left\{ \begin{array}{cc}  1 & & m \equiv 1 \pmod{4}\\ i & & m \equiv 3 \pmod{4}  \end{array}\right. 
 \sum_{x \in \mathbb{Z}/n \mathbb{Z}} e\left(\frac{kx^2}{n} \right)= \gcd(k,n) \sum_{x \in \mathbb{Z}/ n' \mathbb{Z}} e\left(\frac{k' x^2}{n'} \right) 
